  "description": [
    "The Farmville Herald PUBLISHED EVERY TUESDAY AND FRIDAY J B WALL Owner and Publisher Subscriptions Rates In Virginia 1 Year By Mail 300 3 Months By Mail 175 1 Year By Carrier in Farmville 350 1 Month By Carrier in Farmville 35 Subscription Rates Outside Virginia 1 Year 400 With Comics 475 Member Virginia Press Association Member National Editorial Association All communications and monies should be addressed to THE HERALD Farmville Virginia Entered as secondclass matter at the postoffice at Farmville Virginia under Act of Congress of March 3 1879 FRIDAY JANUARY 2 1959 Ise So Confused THE story is told of an old farmer stand ing on a corner twirling a rope He con tinued for some time until a curious passer by stopped and asked what he was doing Tse so confused Some say there will be a war this year some say it wont be Some say hard times are coming some say not Ise so confused that I dont know whether I has found a halter or lost a mule At each New Year the economists politi cians polltakers government officials and editors make so many predictions that most people become just as confused as the"
